modules.description: Provides functions to generate and handle Twirp service implementations from Protocol Buffers definitions, including request parsing, response serialization, and error handling. Works with protobuf-generated types, including service interfaces, request messages, and response messages. Used to build lightweight, RPC-based services such as a calculator that supports operations like addition and division.

provides a server implementation for the Twirp protocol using tiny_httpd, enabling RPC communication over HTTP. it defines request and response structures, along with handlers for processing incoming calls. it supports routing RPC methods to corresponding implementation functions and serializing/deserializing protocol buffers. examples include setting up a server that handles user authentication or data retrieval via defined service methods.
